Note: MicroRuna v0.1 Hello World Example
Note: Demonstrates basic MicroRuna syntax and builtin functions
Note: This is one of the first programs that should compile successfully

Note: Simple greeting function
Process called "greet" that takes name as String returns Void:
    Let greeting be call concat("Hello, ", name)
    Set greeting to call concat(greeting, "!")
    Display greeting
End Process

Note: Main program execution
Let world_message be "Hello, World!"
Display world_message

Note: Demonstrate variables and function calls
Let my_name be "MicroRuna v0.1"
call greet(my_name)

Note: Demonstrate string operations
Let message be "Welcome to MicroRuna!"
Let message_length be call length_of(message)
Let length_text be call concat("Message length: ", call to_string(message_length))
Display length_text

Note: Demonstrate substring operations
Let first_word be call substring(message, 0, 7)
Let substring_text be call concat("First word: ", first_word)
Display substring_text

Note: Demonstrate arithmetic
Let x be 10
Let y be 20
Let sum be x plus y
Let sum_text be call concat("10 + 20 = ", call to_string(sum))
Display sum_text

Note: Demonstrate conditionals
If sum is greater than 25:
    Display "Sum is greater than 25"
Otherwise:
    Display "Sum is 25 or less"
End If

Note: Demonstrate loops
Let counter be 1
Display "Counting to 3:"
While counter is less than 4:
    Let count_text be call concat("Count: ", call to_string(counter))
    Display count_text
    Set counter to counter plus 1
End While

Display "Hello World example completed!"